 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> TOFS?</span><hr size=1> I'm lvl 30 with good gear, Ghoulbane, ION spell and mithril 2hander.<br>
<br>
Can I solo the 1st Lvl. in Tower of Frozen Shadow?<br>
<br>
There was only 2 people in there last night me and one other.<br>
:-(<br>
I went in and there was a lvl 55 there who said I should leave because things under con in there.<br>
I had Invis to undead and ran around and it looked like there were a few spawns that I could single pull to front door for quick escape.<br>
<br>
I left after hearing that from the high lvl guy and went to kill cougars.  BTW I fought a yellow con cougar and someone gave me haste and slowed it(helper was lvl 30) and i got 1/2 a blue bubble from the kill, in Lvl. 30!!  <br>
<br>
Chipp <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udeffcon10.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deffcon10</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42584" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 1:08:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> I do not recommend soloing but its doable while you wait for a few more people<br>
<br>
I do real well recruiting and I would alway try to get one or two more people from IC to come to the first floor of IC.<br>
<br>
While you wait, this is what I suggest.<br>
<br>
You will see the two specters at the end of the door ways.  If you use your undead spell and run back by the mirror only one will come up.  You can take that one with full mana and your ghoulbane.  Depending on how much damage you took you can med and heal and then take the next one out.  This will get you some nice exps.  I remember getting about 1 blue four or six specters.  <br>
<br>
After two you can med and continue to recruit some help.  With one more in the low 30s, you can get start pulling the skeletons but if you really want that key I would try to have three people in the low thirties.  <br>
<br>
Its a safe place to get good exps, not much in terms of loot but it can be fast moving and safe.<br>
<br>
Unless you have four or more stay away from those Beast on the right side of the zone.<br>
<br>
Deffcon DeathBane<br>
51 Level Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitchywhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitchywhon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 1:49:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> &gt;If you use your undead spell <br>
<br>
Which undead spell?<br>
<br>
I guess they run strait across the pit or wont aggro other stuff when they run, um float to me?<br>
<br>
Skeletons con'd dark blue to me<br>
<br>
Chipp Sahoy  Lvl. 30 Dwarf Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tuonolamadargento>Tuono Lamadargento</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 1:56:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> maybe 30 is too low.. but u can try.. the mirror is close but beware when zoning u can aggro some snow guardian.. and at 30 they HURT! <br>
<br>
(i think mith 2hander outdamage GB.. even whit procs)<br>
<br>
try whit expulse undead (but maybe Ward is less resisted at you lvl) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhardedgehopebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hardedge Hopebringer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 1:09:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> Id come back when I was in my 40's. From the 3rd floor down things really do under-con and it can be tough. Me, and a friend got owned trying to fight there at level 40, which only made me want to master the place.<br>
<br>
Its normaly not a hard place to get friends to come to, becuase the XP is amazing, and there are some great drops. Most of the drops are geared towards casters, so its normaly not to hard to get clerics, and enchanters to come along.<br>
<br>
Its a great place to start learning raiding tactics, too. I cut my raid leading teeth by doing 1/2 group mini raids there 2 or 3 nights a week for a long time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Its really a wonderfull zone once you learn all the ways to use the buggy pathing against the MoBs, and learn all the little tricks to pull singles there. There are also ways to force spawn some of the named MoBs there, like killing the ice shade with a pet on floor 6 to force the geni to spawn. <p><I><U><FONT FACE="Copperplate Gothic Bold" COLOR="#000080"><P>Hardedge Hopebringer</P>
</FONT><FONT FACE="Copperplate Gothic Bold" SIZE=2 COLOR="#808080"><P>Knight of Truth and passion</P>
</I></U></FONT><P><A HREF="http://www.crosswinds.net/~wingsofhonor/"><I><FONT FACE="Copperplate Gothic Bold" COLOR="#808080">Wings of honor</I></FONT></A></P>
<I><U><FONT FACE="Copperplate Gothic Bold" SIZE=2 COLOR="#808080"><P>Brell Serilis</P>
</I></U></FONT><FONT FACE="Copperplate Gothic Light" SIZE=1><P>"Capt'n!  The spellchecker kinna take this abuse!"</FONT><FONT FACE="Copperplate Gothic Light"><BR>
</P></FONT></BODY>
</HTML>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/13/02 8:51:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> I personally have not done this because I deem it an exploit, but I have seen it being done several times when I zoned into ToFS. <br>
<br>
With Fear undead if you pull the mobs into the zone in portion of the zone, you can fear them and they run into the wall and cant move. Pretty easy to slice them up then.<br>
<br>
Its a judgement call on your part if you want to use this fear pathing to your advantage or not. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> 
<br>58 Knight of Brell
<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker
</bold>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyermaker>Dyermaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 10:15:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> Soloing at 30 is going to be difficult, mostly because of the pulling. It is very easy to aggro a lot more than you want to pull.<br>
<br>
If this is something you want to try, I would recommend using Undead Fear and sending things running. They will run toward the mirror where you zone in. When they hit the mirror they just keep trying to run straight ahead, so you get to beat on them.<br>
<br>
Be very careful moving around... the sliding floors will get you, and just one bit of lag too long and you can end up in the pit with a lot of company... <p>Dyermaker Merdinho -- The Lost Paladin and Lil'Bastard<BR>
