Profiles: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Magelo<A> -- <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=16712">Allakhazam</A> --
<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3366">Caster's Realm</A><BR>
Lil'Bastard Clan: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Dyermaker</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91012">Chapado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115022">Chiad</A>  | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82578">Malvado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92554">Narnya</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111438">Solyony</A> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utramausvoronadil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tramaus Voronadil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 12:03:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS?</span><hr size=1> Aye, I’d have to agree. Mid 30’s is minimum what I would recommend (and if you have to zone out the guardians are royal pains). And as has been stated, very easy thing to do is just pull near entrance then spook. They’ll run towards the wall and stay there. I personally don’t like this method because:<br>
<br>
1). It feels like an exploit (even if it’s perfectly legal to do it)<br>
2). It spoils you and really does no one any good (especially you).<br>
<br>
But it’s up to you if you want to try and do that. One thing is for sure, the tower is a blast in a group and solo it can get very challenging. Just remember the under con rule of Velious applies here, they hit hard/fast and usually have more HP that you would expect.<br>
<br>
Tramaus Voronadil<br>
45th Paladin of Truth – Order of Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukinammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 4:53:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tofs</span><hr size=1> Just a little FYI, 2nd floor is quite a bit harder than the first. You can die very easily there. The exit for the 2nd floor is hidden behind a bookshelf in the back left portion of the library. I would recommend a pretty full group of 40s there. 2 paladins, 2 clerics, and a chanter, druid. Expect to die there occasionaly. The casters just hurt. <br>
<br>
Be careful there, things can get bad really quick. <br>
<br>
Kinammer IsFunkyFresh<br>
Scions of Veeshan <br>
The Nameless <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujohanhans.showPublicProfile?language=EN>johanhans</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 1:36:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tofs</span><hr size=1> Hm just a side note. Further up in the tower there are some spots that a paladin can solo for good exp. Soloed my low 50s on 6th floor. In order to get there though you need a full set of keys and you need a good group of high 40s or a few low 50s to get key on 4th and 5th floor<br>
<br>
